\frac{1.2t}{3.2}=\frac{\mathrm{shadow}(t)}{1.8}
\mathrm{shadow}(t)=\frac{1.2t}{3.2}\times 1.8=\frac{2.16 t}{3.2}=\frac{27t}{40}.
\frac{d\,\mathrm{shadow}(t)}{dt}=\frac{d}{dt}\left(\frac{27t}{40}\right)=\frac{27}{40}\,\text{m/s}
